# AGENTS.md — JARVIS environment

This file is the canonical per-host source of truth. JARVIS reads it on
demand for environment context — hostname, OS, the user it runs as, what's
running, where things live. The system prompt is intentionally generic;
everything host-specific belongs here.

Hand-curated. The setup script copies this template to `~/.jarvis/AGENTS.md`
on first install; from then on the live copy is yours to edit freely. Keep
it terse and accurate. JARVIS may also edit it at your direction.

## Host
- Hostname: <hostname>
- Hardware: <make/model, e.g. "Lenovo ThinkCentre M710q">
- OS: <distro + version + kernel, e.g. "Ubuntu 24.04 LTS, kernel 6.8">
- Disk / RAM: <quick capacity notes>
- Network: <SSH port, VPN/Tailscale, anything inbound>

## User JARVIS runs as
- <username> (uid <N>)
- Groups: <relevant ones, e.g. sudo, docker>
- Sudo: <passwordless? gated?>
- Home: /home/<username>

## JARVIS layout
- Source: ~/jarvis/   (git repo, replaceable wholesale)
- Data:   ~/.jarvis/  (per-host, never in source)
- Config: ~/.jarvis/config.yaml
- Secrets: ~/.jarvis/.env (chmod 600)
- System prompt: ~/.jarvis/prompts/system.md
- Audit log: ~/.jarvis/data/audit.log
- Sessions: ~/.jarvis/data/sessions/
- Notes: ~/.jarvis/data/notes/

## Services running on this box

### Docker containers
- <name> — <image>, <one-line purpose>. Mount/world/data paths.
- <add as needed; remove when retired>

### Notable systemd services
- <name> — <one-line purpose>
- <run `systemctl list-units --type=service --state=running` for the live list>

## Conventions
- <where projects live, e.g. "Jack's projects: /home/<user>/projects/">
- Code style for JARVIS source: see DESIGN.md in ~/jarvis/.

